# === Block non-site files from being served (added 2026-07-21) =================
# WHY: `pages_build_output_dir = "."` means the ENTIRE repo root is the deploy
# output, so every build/config/working file ships and is publicly readable.
# Confirmed live on 2026-07-21: /deploy.sh, /wrangler.toml, /.gitignore,
# /.atlas/atlas.db (a 340K SQLite DB), /.github/workflows/*.yml, /kit/CLAUDE.md,
# /scripts/audit.py and the internal .md docs all returned 200 — on the apex
# domain AND on the pages.dev preview URL.
#
# WHY REDIRECTS AND NOT AN IGNORE FILE: Cloudflare's own docs document NO upload
# exclusion for `wrangler pages deploy` — no --exclude, no .cfignore, and
# .assetsignore is a Workers Assets feature that Pages does not honour (the
# existing .assetsignore lists *.toml, yet /wrangler.toml served 200). The only
# files Pages itself withholds are _headers and _redirects. Redirects run BEFORE
# static assets are served, so a 301 here means the bytes are never returned.
#
# LIMITS OF THIS FIX: mitigation, not removal. The files are still uploaded and
# still exist in the deployment; this closes the public route only. The durable
# fix is to stop shipping them — move site files under a dedicated output dir
# (e.g. public/) and point pages_build_output_dir at it, so non-site files are
# outside the deploy root entirely.
#
